{{Infobox UK legislation |short_title = Bus Services Act 2017 |type = Act |parliament = Parliament of the United Kingdom |long_title = An Act to make provision about bus services; and for connected purposes. |year = 2017 |citation = 2017 c. 21 |introduced_by = [[Tariq Ahmad, Baron Ahmad of Wimbledon]] |territorial_extent = [[England and Wales]] |royal_assent = 27th April 2017 |commencement = 27th June 2017 |repeal_date = |amends = [[Transport Act 2000]], [[Transport Act 1985]], [[Road Traffic Regulation Act 1984]], [[Local Transport Act 2008]] |amendments = |related_legislation = |repealing_legislation= |status = Current |legislation_history = https://services.parliament.uk/bills/2016-17/busservices/stages.html |use_new_UK-LEG = yes }}
The '''Bus Services Act 2017''' is an [[Act of Parliament|Act]] of the [[Parliament of the United Kingdom]]. It provides for local transport authorities to create partnership schemes to improve bus services in their areas, and to introduce advanced ticketing schemes. The Act also provides for [[Combined Authority|mayoral combined authorities]] to partially re-regulate bus services by creating franchise schemes similar to the one operated by [[Transport for London]]. It, however, prohibits local authorities from reversing complete [[Bus deregulation in Great Britain|bus deregulation]] by forming a [[Municipal bus company|company for the purpose of providing local services]].
