{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2013}} {{Use New Zealand English|date=August 2013}} {{infobox legislation | short_title = Prostitution Reform Act | legislature = [[New Zealand Parliament]] | image = Coat of arms of New Zealand.svg | imagesize = 180px | long_title = | introduced_by = [[Tim Barnett (politician)|Tim Barnett]] | administered_by = Ministry of Justice | datepassed = 25 June 2003 | royal_assent = 27 June 2003 | date_commenced = 28 June 2003 | amendments = | related = [[Massage Parlours Act 1978]] | repeals = | status = Current }}
The '''Prostitution Reform Act 2003''' is an Act of Parliament that decriminalised [[prostitution in New Zealand]]. It has attracted international attention, although its reception has been mixed. The Act repealed the [[Massage Parlours Act 1978]] and the associated regulations.<ref>[http://www.legislation.govt.nz/act/public/2003/0028/latest/DLM198310.html Prostitution Reform Act 2003], Part 4 Miscellaneous provisions</ref>
